                                <title type="desc">De arte praedicatoria</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">nec auctoritatem nimis obscuram</incipit>
                                <explicit>a qua morte idem ipse christus nos liberare dignetur qui cum patre et filio et spiritu sancto viuit et re<supplied reason="omitted">g</supplied>nat per infinita secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                                <note>The first bifolium is missing, and the text begins in the middle of the prologue, after which follows a table of contents; at the end of the quire, the end of <quote>De luctu spirituali</quote> and the beginning of <quote>De gaudio spirituali</quote> are missing. The chapters agree for the most part with those printed by Migne; however, the last chapter, Ad somnolentos, is missing from the manuscript. The manuscript also includes two additional rubrics - <quote>Quomodo sit orandum</quote> and <quote>de septem peticionibus et pluribus que inferius continetur vltimo etc</quote> - the last of which consist of a number of sermons.</note>
                                <colophon>
                                    <locus from="49ra" to="49ra" scheme="folios"/>Explicit summa Magistri Alani de arte predicandi Sub anno domini M<hi rend="super">o</hi> c<hi rend="super">o</hi>c<hi rend="super">o</hi>c<hi rend="super">o</hi> lxx iiii<hi rend="super">o</hi> proximo die sabbato post festum Iacobi gloriosi apostoli Amen</colophon>
