                                <title type="desc">Explanations of biblical vocabulary</title>
                                <incipit>In ewangelio Luci appropinquaret ihesus </incipit>
                                <explicit>timor per quem non audemus aliud facere nisi complacet diuine uoluntati</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="67va" to="90rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Glosses on the Psalms</title>
                                <incipit>Non resurgunt impii iudicio (Ps. 1:5) scilicet ad misericordiam sed ad dampnacionem</incipit>
                                <explicit>per tres quinquagenas iii status ecclesie significantes Amen</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Explicit hoc totum et cetera Finito libro sit laus et gloria christo Amen</finalRubric>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Lemmata – underlined in red – and glosses are presented in running text. Neither every psalm nor every verse of the psalms is included.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107105">RB</title>
                                            <citedRange from="11084" to="11084" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="90rb" to="91vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Exposition of the Decalogue</title>
                                <incipit>Si in preceptis meis ambulaueritis (Lev. 26:3) <gap reason="editorial"/> Secuntur decem precepta domini</incipit>
                                <explicit>Sodomitis offensoribus clerorum hereticis non confessis AMEN</explicit>
                                <note>The exposition ends with a concordance between the ten commandments and the ten plagues of Egypt, and after this a number of tables listing, with their definitions, the ten commandments, the seven cardinal sins, and the works of mercy.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="92va" to="93vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Episcopales et papales casus</title>
                                <incipit>Sciendum est breuiter pro quibus culpis siue casibus ac penitenciis sit penitens ad episcopum remittendus</incipit>
                                <explicit>suprascriptos casus scire debet et de uerbo ad uerbum intelligere debet et cetera et cetera (?)</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Nota episcopales et papales articulos siue casus</finalRubric>
                                <note>
                                    <p> A brief treatise on penance and episcopal and papal absolution with excerpts from Gratian's Decretals. <!--inte 100% på detta...-->
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="92r" to="92r" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
